<subSubSection id="24DC108B5E58C516FF3FBA21FD37EDB8" lastPageId="91" lastPageNumber="92" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="6C7943005E58C517FF3FBA21FDB7E8F9" blockId="90.[151,1437,1186,2002]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E58C517FF3FBA21FE97E820" bold="true" box="[199,321,1330,1355]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
One of two 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E58C517FE35BA20FD89E820" authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" box="[461,607,1331,1355]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Medeopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E58C517FE35BA20FD89E820" box="[461,607,1331,1355]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Medeopteryx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with trisinuate V7 but without deflexed elytral apices; distinguished most from 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E58C517FF25BA44FE66E805" authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" box="[221,432,1366,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Medeopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similispupillae">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E58C517FF25BA44FE66E805" box="[221,432,1366,1390]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">M. similispupillae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the pale terminal abdominal tergites (
<figureCitation id="F4FD5F855E58C517FC40BA45FBF7E805" box="[952,1057,1366,1390]" captionStart="FIGURES 168–176" captionStartId="79.[151,263,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[192,1388,181,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-68@79.[192,1400,181,1909]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="FIGURES 168–176. Medeopteryx pupilla male Mt Lamington (AMUS). 168 dorsal; 169, 170 abdomen ventral (169) and dorsal; 171–173 aedeagus left lateral, dorsolateral and ventral; 174, 175 tergite 8 (174 ventral with aedeagal sheath; 175 from right side, dorsal surface uppermost, flanges arrowed); 176 aedeagal sheath dorsal. These figures share scale lines: 171–173." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265410/files/figure.png" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Fig. 170</figureCitation>
) and the broader ML (that of 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E58C517FF6FBA68FEEAE8F8" authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" box="[151,316,1403,1427]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Medeopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similispupillae">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E58C517FF6FBA68FEEAE8F8" box="[151,316,1403,1427]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">similispupillae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very narrow; 
<figureCitation id="F4FD5F855E58C517FE0BBA69FD82E8F9" box="[499,596,1402,1426]" captionStart="FIGURES 177–184" captionStartId="80.[151,263,1305,1328]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,187,1285]" captionTargetId="figure-310@80.[151,1436,187,1285]" captionTargetPageId="80" captionText="FIGURES 177–184. Medeopteryx spp. Males. 177–182 M. similispupillae sp. nov. paratypes. 183 M. torricelliensis. 184 M. sublustris, diagrammatic representation of pronotal sculpturing. 177, 183 dorsal; 178, 179 abdomen, ventral (178) and dorsal; 180–182 aedeagus dorsal (180), left lateral (181) and ventral (182). These figures share scale lines: 180–182" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265414" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265414/files/figure.png" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Fig. 182</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6C7943005E58C516FF3FBA8CFD37EDB8" blockId="90.[151,1437,1186,2002]" lastBlockId="91.[151,1436,151,572]" lastPageId="91" lastPageNumber="92" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E58C517FF3FBA8CFEDCE8DC" bold="true" box="[199,266,1439,1463]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Male.</emphasis>
5.3 (
<typeStatus id="B37DFDA25E58C517FEB6BA8DFE6EE8DD" box="[334,440,1438,1462]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">lectotype</typeStatus>
)– 
<quantity id="AB3EEEE55E58C517FE35BA8DFDFEE8DD" box="[461,552,1438,1462]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.7" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" unit="mm" value="7.7">7.7 mm</quantity>
long. Colour (
<figureCitation id="F4FD5F855E58C517FD24BA8DFC92E8DD" box="[732,836,1438,1462]" captionStart="FIGURES 168–176" captionStartId="79.[151,263,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[192,1388,181,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-68@79.[192,1400,181,1909]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="FIGURES 168–176. Medeopteryx pupilla male Mt Lamington (AMUS). 168 dorsal; 169, 170 abdomen ventral (169) and dorsal; 171–173 aedeagus left lateral, dorsolateral and ventral; 174, 175 tergite 8 (174 ventral with aedeagal sheath; 175 from right side, dorsal surface uppermost, flanges arrowed); 176 aedeagal sheath dorsal. These figures share scale lines: 171–173." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265410/files/figure.png" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Fig. 168</figureCitation>
): pronotum dingy orange (finely dark margined in G141); MS dingy orange, marked in brown in anterior half; MN cream; elytra uniformly very dark brown, reddish brown with narrowly pale margins in one Mt Lamington male; head between eyes, antennae and palpi almost black (head of G148 appearing paler brown as semitransparent cuticle reveals underlying fat body); entire ventral surface of thorax, all of legs 1–3 dark brown (coxae and base of femora of legs 1, 2 orange in one Mt Lamington male); basal abdominal ventrites dark brown; V5–7 dirty white (1/4 to ½ of posterior area of V5 pale in Mt Lamington males; T2–6 yellow (
<typeStatus id="B37DFDA25E58C517FE7FB965FE25EBE5" box="[391,499,1654,1678]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">lectotype</typeStatus>
), brownish in Mt Lamington males, semitransparent, T7–8 white, semitransparent. Pronotum: 1.3 (
<typeStatus id="B37DFDA25E58C517FEADB989FE68EBD9" box="[341,446,1690,1714]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">lectotype</typeStatus>
)– 
<quantity id="AB3EEEE55E58C517FE2CB989FDE7EBD9" box="[468,561,1690,1714]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.2 mm</quantity>
wide, 1.0 (
<typeStatus id="B37DFDA25E58C517FD3EB989FCE7EBD9" box="[710,817,1690,1714]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">lectotype</typeStatus>
)– 
<quantity id="AB3EEEE55E58C517FCBFB989FC74EBD9" box="[839,930,1690,1714]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" unit="mm" value="1.4">1.4 mm</quantity>
long, W/L = 1.4–1.7; punctures shallow, contiguous across anterior and lateral margins, separated by up to their width over central area of disc; midanterior margin broadly rounded, moderately projecting beyond rounded anterolateral corners, with lateral margins subparallel, converging slightly in anterior and posterior third in 
<typeStatus id="B37DFDA25E58C517FC66B815FBDEEA75" box="[926,1032,1798,1822]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">lectotype</typeStatus>
; lateral margins divergent slightly posteriorly, with anterolateral and posterolateral corners angulate in Mt Lamington males. Head: GHW 1.1(
<typeStatus id="B37DFDA25E58C517FF46B85DFEFAEA0D" box="[190,300,1870,1894]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">lectotype</typeStatus>
)– 
<quantity id="AB3EEEE55E58C517FEBBB85DFE4CEA0D" box="[323,410,1870,1894]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" unit="mm" value="1.8">1.8 mm</quantity>
, SIW 
<quantity id="AB3EEEE55E58C517FE1BB85DFDEBEA0D" box="[483,573,1870,1894]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.2 mm</quantity>
; ASD slightly &lt;ASW. FS elongate, slender, subequal. Abdomen (
<figureCitation id="F4FD5F855E58C517FAC9B85DFEEEEAE1" captionStart="FIGURES 168–176" captionStartId="79.[151,263,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[192,1388,181,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-68@79.[192,1400,181,1909]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="FIGURES 168–176. Medeopteryx pupilla male Mt Lamington (AMUS). 168 dorsal; 169, 170 abdomen ventral (169) and dorsal; 171–173 aedeagus left lateral, dorsolateral and ventral; 174, 175 tergite 8 (174 ventral with aedeagal sheath; 175 from right side, dorsal surface uppermost, flanges arrowed); 176 aedeagal sheath dorsal. These figures share scale lines: 171–173." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265410/files/figure.png" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Figs 169, 170, 175, 176</figureCitation>
): LOs occupying all of V6 and 7 except for narrow posterior margin of 7; MPP moderately broad, longer than wide, apically truncate (
<typeStatus id="B37DFDA25E58C517FDD7B885FD4FEAC5" box="[559,665,1942,1966]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">lectotype</typeStatus>
) or slightly emarginated, longer and wider than PLP, T8 with broad short rounded flanges in 
<typeStatus id="B37DFDA25E58C517FE53B8A9FDC3EAB9" box="[427,533,1978,2002]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">lectotype</typeStatus>
; flanges about as long as wide and apically truncate in Mt Lamington males (
<figureCitation id="F4FD5F855E58C516FA96B8A9FF12EDC4" captionStart="FIGURES 168–176" captionStartId="79.[151,263,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[192,1388,181,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-68@79.[192,1400,181,1909]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="FIGURES 168–176. Medeopteryx pupilla male Mt Lamington (AMUS). 168 dorsal; 169, 170 abdomen ventral (169) and dorsal; 171–173 aedeagus left lateral, dorsolateral and ventral; 174, 175 tergite 8 (174 ventral with aedeagal sheath; 175 from right side, dorsal surface uppermost, flanges arrowed); 176 aedeagal sheath dorsal. These figures share scale lines: 171–173." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265410/files/figure.png" lastPageId="91" lastPageNumber="92" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Fig. 175</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus: (
<figureCitation id="F4FD5F855E59C516FEA4BF84FE21EDC4" box="[348,503,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURES 168–176" captionStartId="79.[151,263,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[192,1388,181,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-68@79.[192,1400,181,1909]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="FIGURES 168–176. Medeopteryx pupilla male Mt Lamington (AMUS). 168 dorsal; 169, 170 abdomen ventral (169) and dorsal; 171–173 aedeagus left lateral, dorsolateral and ventral; 174, 175 tergite 8 (174 ventral with aedeagal sheath; 175 from right side, dorsal surface uppermost, flanges arrowed); 176 aedeagal sheath dorsal. These figures share scale lines: 171–173." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265410/files/figure.png" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Figs 171–173</figureCitation>
) ML expanded, and may appear concave in posterior half, 0.7 as wide as LL across narrowest portion of ML; LL inturned at inner apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="24DC108B5E59C516FF3FBFF3FB35EF57" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6C7943005E59C516FF3FBFF3FB06EC77" blockId="91.[151,1436,151,572]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E59C516FF3FBFF3FEEDED93" bold="true" box="[199,315,224,248]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Remarks.</emphasis>
Confusion in the literature over the identity of 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E59C516FC8CBFF3FBF2ED93" authorityName="Olivier. Ballantyne &amp; McLean" authorityYear="1970" box="[884,1060,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pupilla">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E59C516FC8CBFF3FBF2ED93" box="[884,1060,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Luciola pupilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is resolved by designation of a 
<typeStatus id="B37DFDA25E59C516FF6FBE17FF2BEC77" box="[151,253,260,284]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">lectotype</typeStatus>
(first in a 
<typeStatus id="B37DFDA25E59C516FE8ABE17FE1FEC77" box="[370,457,260,284]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">syntype</typeStatus>
series). 
<bibRefCitation id="08573EF15E59C516FDD0BE17FD2DEC77" author="McDermott, F. A." box="[552,763,260,284]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" pagination="98 - 118" refId="ref127730" refString="McDermott, F. A. (1966) Lampyridae Pars. 9. Coleopterorum Catalogus (Junk-Schenkling) (Ed. Sec), 1 - 149 (Luciolini, 98 - 118)." type="book chapter" year="1966">McDermott (1966)</bibRefCitation>
incorrectly assigned 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E59C516FC12BE17FBEFEC77" authorityName="Olivier. Ballantyne &amp; McLean" authorityYear="1970" box="[1002,1081,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pupilla">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E59C516FC12BE17FBEFEC77" box="[1002,1081,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">pupilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E59C516FBA5BE16FB06EC77" box="[1117,1232,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E59C516FBA5BE16FB1AEC77" box="[1117,1228,261,284]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pteroptyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pteroptyx</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6C7943005E59C516FF3FBE3BFE4AECE3" blockId="91.[151,1436,151,572]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
LB tentatively identified 
<bibRefCitation id="08573EF15E59C516FE1EBE34FD4EEC54" author="Lloyd, J. E." box="[486,664,295,319]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" pagination="991 - 1008" refId="ref127038" refString="Lloyd, J. E. (1973 a) Fireflies of Melanesia: Bioluminescence, Mating Behavior, and Synchronous flashing. Environmental Entomology, 2 (no. 6), 991 - 1008." type="journal article" year="1973">Lloyd's (1973a)</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E59C516FD59BE3BFC86EC54" box="[673,848,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E59C516FD59BE3BFD21EC2B" box="[673,759,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Luciola</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
11 as 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E59C516FC64BE3BFB9FEC2B" authorityName="Olivier. Ballantyne &amp; McLean" authorityYear="1970" box="[924,1097,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pupilla">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E59C516FC64BE3BFB9FEC2B" box="[924,1097,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Luciola pupilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and abdominal modifications were described (
<bibRefCitation id="08573EF15E59C516FEB6BE5FFDC8EC0F" author="Ballantyne, L. A." box="[334,542,332,356]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" pagination="117 - 170" refId="ref122195" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. (1987 a) Further Revisional Studies on the firefly genus Pteroptyx Olivier (Coleoptera: Lampyridae: Luciolinae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 113, 117 - 170." type="journal article" year="1987">Ballantyne, 1987a</bibRefCitation>
, b). This study has revealed two species with similar V7, viz. 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E59C516FB2BBE5EFA91EC0F" authorityName="Olivier. Ballantyne &amp; McLean" authorityYear="1970" box="[1235,1351,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pupilla">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E59C516FB2BBE5EFA91EC0F" box="[1235,1351,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">M. pupilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E59C516FA85BE5EFEEAECE3" authority="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin, 2013" authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Medeopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similispupillae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E59C516FA85BE5EFEEAECE3" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">M. similispupillae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E59C516FEBBBE63FE4AECE3" bold="true" box="[323,412,368,392]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="458122695E59C516FEBBBE63FE4AECE3" box="[323,412,368,392]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6C7943005E59C516FF3FBE87FED1EF7C" blockId="91.[151,1436,151,572]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
It is now possible to determine an approximate location for &quot;Ighibirei&quot; which is also the 
<typeStatus id="B37DFDA25E59C516FB11BE87FACFECC7" box="[1257,1305,404,428]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E59C516FF6FBEABFDDFECA4" authority="(Olivier)" authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[151,521,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Medeopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cribellata">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E59C516FF6FBEABFE4BECBB" box="[151,413,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Medeopteryx cribellata</emphasis>
(Olivier)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="08573EF15E59C516FDEABEA4FD25ECA4" author="Helgen, K. &amp; Leary, T. &amp; Doria G. &amp; Amori, G." box="[530,755,439,464]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" pagination="653 - 686" refId="ref126041" refString="Helgen, K. M, Leary, T., Doria G., &amp; Amori, G. (2008) Catalogue of Melanesian rodents in the Museum of Genova (Mammalia: Rodentia). Annali del Museo Civico di Storia naturale G. Doria, 99, 653 - 686." type="journal article" year="2008">
Helgen 
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E59C516FD92BEAAFD74ECBB" box="[618,674,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
referred to Loria’s collecting locality as either “on the Kemp Welch river some little way inland “or “ just inland from the mouth of the Wanigela River”. The elevation is unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6C7943005E59C516FF3FBD37FB35EF57" blockId="91.[151,1436,151,572]" box="[199,1251,548,572]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Lloyd's field records for specimen G148 read &quot;slow double pulse signal, one second interval&quot;.</paragraph>
